01:12:23,768 --> 01:12:27,600
- What does she want from you?
- She's broke.

779
01:12:27,647 --> 01:12:30,352
She wants a reward for the album.

780
01:12:30,400 --> 01:12:32,689
Or she collects photos, too.

781
01:12:32,736 --> 01:12:37,030
She wants to trade us
for a one-eyed man with glasses!

782
01:12:41,703 --> 01:12:42,734
No, you dope!

783
01:12:44,289 --> 01:12:46,661
She's in love.

784
01:12:46,708 --> 01:12:49,459
- I don't even know her.
- Yes, you do.

785
01:12:49,502 --> 01:12:51,329
Since when?

786
01:12:51,379 --> 01:12:53,123
You've always known her.

787
01:12:53,173 --> 01:12:54,453
In your dreams.

788
01:13:07,395 --> 01:13:08,973
Hello?

789
01:13:09,022 --> 01:13:13,102
Yes. You! Man with the plastic bag! It's for you.

790
01:13:14,653 --> 01:13:16,112
- Me?
- Yes.

791
01:13:19,449 --> 01:13:20,480
Thank you.

792
01:13:22,452 --> 01:13:23,483
Hello?

793
01:13:23,536 --> 01:13:26,288
Follow the blue arrows, Mr. Quincampoix.

794
01:14:51,583 --> 01:14:56,044
When the finger's pointing to the sky,
only a fool looks at the finger.

795
01:16:08,576 --> 01:16:09,608
Hello?

796
01:16:10,662 --> 01:16:12,987
I know the stranger in the pictures.

797
01:16:13,039 --> 01:16:17,120
He's a ghost. He's invisible, Mr. Quincampoix.

798
01:16:17,169 --> 01:16:20,538
He only appears when the film is developed.

799
01:16:20,589 --> 01:16:23,958
When a girl has her photo taken,

800
01:16:24,009 --> 01:16:29,963
he goes "Oooh!" in her ear,
while he gently caresses her neck.

801
01:16:30,015 --> 01:16:32,588
That's how he got caught, Mr. Quincampoix.

802
01:16:36,312 --> 01:16:37,594
Who are you?

803
01:16:37,648 --> 01:16:39,107
Page 51.

804
01:16:47,699 --> 01:16:49,277
[DO YOU

805
01:16:49,326 --> 01:16:51,152
WANT

806
01:16:51,202 --> 01:16:53,658
TO MEET ME?]

807
01:18:31,679 --> 01:18:34,514
Listen to this. "A boy of six,

808
01:18:34,556 --> 01:18:36,715
while his parents sleep, drives off

809
01:18:36,767 --> 01:18:38,510
in a pedal car.

810
01:18:38,560 --> 01:18:42,261
Found on a motorway
near Münster in Germany,

811
01:18:42,314 --> 01:18:45,896
he told the police he wanted to see the stars."

812
01:18:45,942 --> 01:18:49,607
Isn't life beautiful, eh?

813
01:18:49,654 --> 01:18:54,233
Love. The only bug she hadn't caught!

814
01:18:54,285 --> 01:18:57,321
- Nobody's immune.
- At least it gives me a break.

815
01:18:57,371 --> 01:18:59,577
Love's a great beautician.

816
01:19:01,792 --> 01:19:05,243
What's she like? Tall? Small? Blonde? Dark?

817
01:19:07,672 --> 01:19:09,748
Let's say... average height.

818
01:19:11,009 --> 01:19:14,046
Not a dwarf or a giraffe. Normal.

819
01:19:15,431 --> 01:19:17,672
Pretty, for her type.

820
01:19:17,725 --> 01:19:20,050
As for blonde or dark...

821
01:19:21,645 --> 01:19:24,729
...it's hard to say, but she wasn't a redhead.

822
01:19:24,773 --> 01:19:26,647
- Unless...
- Forget it.

823
01:19:27,776 --> 01:19:32,651
I do remember she casually asked
if you had a girlfriend.

824
01:19:32,697 --> 01:19:33,728
And?

825
01:19:33,782 --> 01:19:36,238
I said you weren't interested, right?

826
01:19:37,661 --> 01:19:39,156
You didn't!

827
01:19:39,205 --> 01:19:41,446
What do you care? You don't even know her.

828
01:19:42,499 --> 01:19:46,711
- Exactly. It's the mystery.
- You won't find mystery here.

829
01:19:46,753 --> 01:19:48,960
A pound of nectarines, please.

830
01:19:49,006 --> 01:19:51,841
These ones here are the prettiest.

831
01:19:51,883 --> 01:19:54,006
Trust him. He's an artist!

832
01:19:54,052 --> 01:19:57,136
He's been going home every night
with tons of unsold stock.

833
01:19:57,180 --> 01:20:00,348
What for? Is he stewing a pig?

834
01:20:00,392 --> 01:20:02,551
No, sir! He's studying art!

835
01:20:02,603 --> 01:20:06,303
He sells leeks all day long
and paints turnips all night!

836
01:20:06,356 --> 01:20:08,432
The boy's a useless vegetable.

837
01:20:08,484 --> 01:20:09,978
A good prompter

838
01:20:10,027 --> 01:20:13,609
in each cellar window
whispering cutting retorts

839
01:20:13,655 --> 01:20:16,276
would mean shy people had the last laugh.

840
01:20:16,324 --> 01:20:18,780
At least you'll never be a vegetable.

841
01:20:18,827 --> 01:20:21,069
Even artichokes

842
01:20:21,122 --> 01:20:22,153
have hearts.

843
01:20:25,167 --> 01:20:28,785
You'll never be a vegetable.
Even artichokes have hearts!

844
01:21:10,212 --> 01:21:11,837
Memory seven.

845
01:21:29,523 --> 01:21:33,770
Darling Mado,
I miss you more and more each day.

846
01:21:33,819 --> 01:21:37,105
I'm an exile in a world of dreary khaki.

847
01:21:37,156 --> 01:21:39,444
I can't sleep, can't eat...

848
01:21:39,491 --> 01:21:42,196
This camp was the biggest mistake of my life,

849
01:21:42,244 --> 01:21:46,028
depriving me of my beloved
for five long weeks.

850
01:21:46,081 --> 01:21:48,951
I think of you endlessly. Your Adrien.

851
01:21:50,710 --> 01:21:55,503
I turned down my last month's wages
instead of giving notice.

852
01:21:56,550 --> 01:21:59,884
I dream of better times ahead.

853
01:21:59,928 --> 01:22:03,926
An orange-coloured day. Remember, my love?

854
01:22:03,974 --> 01:22:06,050
Your ever-loving Adrien.

855
01:22:07,853 --> 01:22:09,263
Good news, darling Mado.

856
01:22:09,312 --> 01:22:12,646
Soon I'll be able to afford a car

857
01:22:12,691 --> 01:22:15,183
and drive home every night.

858
01:22:15,236 --> 01:22:19,648
Till then, meet me on Friday and we'll go out.

859
01:25:06,615 --> 01:25:08,821
[MOTHER]

860
01:25:11,662 --> 01:25:13,738
Psychiatric Helpline.

861
01:25:15,291 --> 01:25:17,367
Hello? Hello?

862
01:25:46,113 --> 01:25:48,569
[WHERE & WHEN?]

863
01:25:58,292 --> 01:26:00,748
One hour later at 11 Boulevard St Martin,

864
01:26:00,795 --> 01:26:04,413
Amélie walks into a party goods
and costume shop.

865
01:26:05,466 --> 01:26:09,927
At the same time,
a man leaves his home at 108 Rue Lecourbe.

866
01:26:11,889 --> 01:26:15,637
26 minutes later, Amélie is at the photo booth
at the Gare de I'Est.

867
01:26:19,896 --> 01:26:23,977
Simultaneously,
the man in red shoes parks outside.

868
01:26:24,026 --> 01:26:27,395
The time is exactly 11:40.

869
01:27:13,034 --> 01:27:15,110
At this precise moment,

870
01:27:15,161 --> 01:27:19,906
only Amélie has the key
to the riddle of the mystery man.

871
01:27:24,795 --> 01:27:26,503
How's it going, Mrs. Wells?

872
01:27:26,547 --> 01:27:29,383
It's always better when it's not raining.

873
01:27:29,425 --> 01:27:31,881
- This is for you.
- Me?

874
01:27:41,812 --> 01:27:45,513
Dear Mrs. Wells,
We recently recovered a mailbag

875
01:27:45,566 --> 01:27:47,642
that was lost in a plane crash

876
01:27:47,693 --> 01:27:51,359
on October 12th 1969 on Mont Blanc.

877
01:27:51,406 --> 01:27:55,866
We are forwarding the enclosed letter
to your address.

878
01:27:55,910 --> 01:28:00,073
Please accept our apologies
for the uncustomary delay.

879
01:28:00,122 --> 01:28:02,827
Jacques Grosjean, Customer Services.

880
01:28:04,168 --> 01:28:08,462
Darling Mado, I'm in exile.
I can't sleep, can't eat.

881
01:28:08,505 --> 01:28:10,249
I think of you endlessly.

882
01:28:10,299 --> 01:28:14,167
I know I've made
the biggest mistake of my life.

883
01:28:14,220 --> 01:28:16,925
I turned down that woman's money.

884
01:28:16,973 --> 01:28:21,931
If all goes well,
I'll soon be able to afford a house.

885
01:28:21,978 --> 01:28:25,014
I dream of better times ahead

886
01:28:25,064 --> 01:28:28,931
when you'll forgive me and join me here

887
01:28:28,984 --> 01:28:32,353
one orange-coloured day.
Your ever-loving Adrien.

888
01:29:02,185 --> 01:29:04,343
Mr. Dufayel, another package for you.

889
01:29:14,154 --> 01:29:17,404
Mr. Dufayel, do you know
what happened to the concierge?

890
01:29:18,826 --> 01:29:20,155
She got a letter.

891
01:29:21,204 --> 01:29:24,039
From her husband. 40 years late.

892
01:29:26,376 --> 01:29:28,451
That's a lot, isn't it, Mr. Dufayel?

893
01:29:41,682 --> 01:29:45,134
I'm not big on still life, Mr. Dufayel.

894
01:29:45,186 --> 01:29:48,187
Then work on your thin layer.

895
01:29:48,231 --> 01:29:50,982
Fat over thin. Always!

896
01:30:09,836 --> 01:30:11,627
- Mr. Dufayel...
- Yes!

897
01:30:11,671 --> 01:30:16,048
The papers said
that there'll soon be a new star.

898
01:30:16,092 --> 01:30:23,221
- So you're into stars now?
- I saw it on TV at my mum's, that's why.

899
01:30:25,059 --> 01:30:26,802
I don't know if it's true.

900
01:30:26,852 --> 01:30:29,178
In America

901
01:30:29,230 --> 01:30:32,516
they're going to take all the rich people's ashes,

902
01:30:32,567 --> 01:30:35,236
put them in a satellite

903
01:30:35,278 --> 01:30:37,603
and shoot it into space.

904
01:30:37,655 --> 01:30:40,027
The satellite's going to shine for ever.

905
01:30:44,662 --> 01:30:46,204
And Lady Di...

906
01:30:46,247 --> 01:30:48,488
Will they do the same for her?

907
01:30:48,540 --> 01:30:49,572
Lady Di, Lady Di!

908
01:30:49,626 --> 01:30:50,871
Give it a rest!

909
01:30:50,919 --> 01:30:53,670
I can't concentrate.

910
01:30:55,840 --> 01:30:56,871
Lady Di!

911
01:30:57,967 --> 01:30:58,998
Lady Di!

912
01:31:00,219 --> 01:31:01,250
Renoir.

913
01:32:42,572 --> 01:32:43,603
Morning, sir.

914
01:33:00,339 --> 01:33:01,370
Cambodia.

915
01:33:06,972 --> 01:33:08,715
I don't understand.

916
01:33:08,765 --> 01:33:12,632
Brilliant! You couldn't have done better.

917
01:33:12,685 --> 01:33:15,888
- Did it work?
- It's getting there.

918
01:33:15,938 --> 01:33:18,856
Ask me again any time. The harm's done.

919
01:33:18,900 --> 01:33:22,565
- What do you mean?
- Everybody calls me Snow White!

920
01:34:28,302 --> 01:34:31,137
[The Two Windmills café from 4pm.]

921
01:34:37,646 --> 01:34:39,555
- Eva?
- Yes?

922
01:34:39,606 --> 01:34:43,354
Could you stand in for me at four?

923
01:34:43,401 --> 01:34:45,310
Again?

924
01:34:48,656 --> 01:34:50,115
Close the door!

925
01:34:52,285 --> 01:34:54,277
What's up with him?

926
01:34:54,328 --> 01:34:56,072
Is he sulking?

927
01:34:56,122 --> 01:34:59,705
- He thinks I smile too much.
- He'd rather you frowned?

928
01:34:59,751 --> 01:35:02,668
With other men, yes.

929
01:35:05,381 --> 01:35:09,794
Nino is late. Amélie can only think
of two possible explanations.

930
01:35:09,844 --> 01:35:11,920
Firstly, that he didn't find the photo.

931
01:35:13,764 --> 01:35:16,220
Secondly, before he could assemble it,

932
01:35:16,267 --> 01:35:20,562
a gang of bank robbers took him hostage.

933
01:35:20,605 --> 01:35:22,598
The cops gave chase.

934
01:35:22,649 --> 01:35:24,440
They got away,

935
01:35:24,484 --> 01:35:27,236
but he caused a crash.

936
01:35:27,278 --> 01:35:29,485
When he came to,

937
01:35:29,531 --> 01:35:31,190
he'd lost his memory,

938
01:35:33,076 --> 01:35:34,949
An ex-con picked him up,

939
01:35:34,994 --> 01:35:39,205
mistook him for a fugitive,
and shipped him to Istanbul.

940
01:35:40,166 --> 01:35:42,408
He met some Afghan raiders,

941
01:35:42,461 --> 01:35:46,043
who took him to steal
some Russian warheads.

942
01:35:49,676 --> 01:35:53,508
But their truck hit a mine
at the border with Tajikistan.

943
01:35:53,555 --> 01:35:59,059
He survived, took to the hills,
and became a Mujaheddin.

944
01:35:59,102 --> 01:36:02,055
Amélie refuses to get upset for a guy

945
01:36:02,104 --> 01:36:06,684
who'll eat borscht all his life
in a hat like a tea cosy.

946
01:36:25,920 --> 01:36:28,127
- What can I get you?
- A coffee, please.

947
01:36:29,216 --> 01:36:31,089
A coffee.

948
01:36:53,115 --> 01:36:54,573
Here's your coffee.

949
01:36:56,117 --> 01:36:57,149
Thank you.

950
01:37:20,850 --> 01:37:23,176
[Today's menu]

951
01:37:32,195 --> 01:37:33,653
He's understood.

952
01:37:33,696 --> 01:37:36,900
He's going to put his teaspoon down,

953
01:37:38,326 --> 01:37:41,909
dip his finger in the sugar,

954
01:37:46,668 --> 01:37:49,372
turn around slowly,

955
01:37:49,420 --> 01:37:51,496
and speak to me.

956
01:37:57,095 --> 01:37:59,088
Excuse me.

957
01:38:00,599 --> 01:38:01,844
Is this you?

958
01:38:08,314 --> 01:38:09,559
Yes, it's you.

959
01:38:30,253 --> 01:38:32,329
I'll take that.

960
01:38:34,757 --> 01:38:36,417
Another coffee?

961
01:38:36,467 --> 01:38:38,590
- No, thanks. I'm fine.
- OK.

962
01:38:59,157 --> 01:39:03,618
So it's this man here,
the one with his hand up?

963
01:39:04,872 --> 01:39:05,903
Yes.

964
01:39:08,250 --> 01:39:11,120
Is she in love with him?

965
01:39:13,922 --> 01:39:14,953
Yes.

966
01:39:16,883 --> 01:39:20,252
I think it's time she took a real risk.

967
01:39:20,303 --> 01:39:24,799
She might just do that.
She's devising a stratagem.

968
01:39:24,849 --> 01:39:28,515
She's fond of stratagems.

969
01:39:30,564 --> 01:39:31,595
Yes.

970
01:39:33,316 --> 01:39:35,439
In fact, she's cowardly.

971
01:39:36,820 --> 01:39:40,189
That's why I can't capture her look.

972
01:39:42,033 --> 01:39:47,537
Dufayel's attempts to meddle are intolerable!

973
01:39:50,042 --> 01:39:55,996
If Amélie chooses to live in a dream

974
01:39:56,048 --> 01:40:00,259
and remain an introverted young woman,

975
01:40:00,302 --> 01:40:04,963
she has an absolute right to mess up her life!

976
01:40:39,716 --> 01:40:41,460
What are you doing, Mr. Dufayel?

977
01:40:43,845 --> 01:40:45,968
Tell me, Lucien.

978
01:40:46,014 --> 01:40:50,889
For deliveries,
do you keep keys to all the apartments?

979
01:41:03,365 --> 01:41:07,232
One of your booths is out of order.

980
01:41:09,371 --> 01:41:11,909
It seems to be jammed.

981
01:41:13,041 --> 01:41:15,329
Gare de I'Est ticket hall.

982
01:41:18,171 --> 01:41:20,544
- Buy a video, get one free.
- No, thanks.

983
01:41:27,305 --> 01:41:28,965
Sam?

984
01:41:30,016 --> 01:41:31,048
Samantha?

985
01:41:34,396 --> 01:41:35,427
Samantha?

986
01:41:40,360 --> 01:41:42,270
Can you stand in for me at...

987
01:42:04,718 --> 01:42:08,383
Photo booth, Gare de I'Est ticket hall,
Tuesday 5pm.

988
01:42:08,430 --> 01:42:11,764
[Can you stand in for me this afternoon?]

989
01:43:23,005 --> 01:43:24,333
Almost done.

990
01:43:29,469 --> 01:43:33,515
The mystery man wasn't a ghost
or a man scared of ageing,

991
01:43:33,557 --> 01:43:35,633
but simply the repairman,

992
01:43:35,684 --> 01:43:38,140
a normal guy doing his job.

993
01:43:40,272 --> 01:43:41,932
Sorry.

994
01:44:27,569 --> 01:44:30,938
He keeps spying on me!
It's making me sick.

995
01:44:30,989 --> 01:44:34,405
4:05: Blatant female conspiracy.

996
01:44:35,452 --> 01:44:38,903
Gosh, you're tense, Georgette!

997
01:44:39,956 --> 01:44:41,499
Good luck. You'll need it.

998
01:44:46,922 --> 01:44:51,500
Excuse me. Did you put this in my pocket?

999
01:44:51,552 --> 01:44:54,967
- Yes, but I'm not the one...
- I know. Where is she?

1000
01:44:55,013 --> 01:44:56,555
She's at her father's.

1001
01:44:56,598 --> 01:45:02,019
It's awkward. I'd like to speak to you, but...
I finish work at six.

1002
01:45:02,062 --> 01:45:04,020
- Can you come back?
- OK.

1003
01:45:05,065 --> 01:45:06,145
See you later.

1004
01:45:06,192 --> 01:45:09,774
4:08: Docking scheduled.

1005
01:45:41,601 --> 01:45:46,263
The blond guy in a camel coat.
He's very absent-minded, too.

1006
01:45:46,314 --> 01:45:48,059
How come?

1007
01:45:49,110 --> 01:45:51,565
He came back three times the same afternoon.

1008
01:45:52,821 --> 01:45:54,102
1:12:

1009
01:45:54,156 --> 01:45:55,436
Camel coat.

1010
01:45:55,491 --> 01:45:56,736
2:50:

1011
01:45:56,784 --> 01:45:58,610
Camel coat.

1012
01:45:58,660 --> 01:46:00,867
- 4:17: Camel coat.
- Stop it!

1013
01:46:01,914 --> 01:46:05,117
My rash has come back! Look, Suzanne!

1014
01:46:05,167 --> 01:46:08,867
My rash is back. He's driving me nuts.

1015
01:46:08,920 --> 01:46:11,080
Lay off!

1016
01:46:11,132 --> 01:46:15,425
If she had a clear conscience,
she wouldn't be in such a state.

1017
01:46:15,469 --> 01:46:17,426
I've had it. I'm going home.

1018
01:46:17,471 --> 01:46:20,970
Psychos are the last straw!

1019
01:46:22,351 --> 01:46:24,390
Georgette! Georg...

1020
01:46:25,979 --> 01:46:28,731
Stop smothering them!
Women need to breathe.

1021
01:46:28,774 --> 01:46:32,059
You let them breathe,
they want a change of air.

1022
01:46:32,110 --> 01:46:33,985
Fresh air's healthy.

1023
01:46:34,030 --> 01:46:36,022
Shut it, failure!

1024
01:46:38,576 --> 01:46:40,283
Failed writer, failed life...

1025
01:46:40,327 --> 01:46:42,901
I love the word "fail".

1026
01:46:42,955 --> 01:46:44,994
Failure is human destiny.

1027
01:46:45,040 --> 01:46:46,618
It's gasbag time!

1028
01:46:46,667 --> 01:46:49,917
Failure teaches us that life is but a draft,

1029
01:46:49,961 --> 01:46:53,829
a long rehearsal for a show that will never play.

1030
01:46:55,259 --> 01:46:57,584
I bet he stole that.

1031
01:46:57,637 --> 01:47:00,127
I do have some original ideas,

1032
01:47:00,181 --> 01:47:05,637
but people always steal them.
A bit like your women.

1033
01:47:05,686 --> 01:47:07,725
Meaning?

1034
01:47:07,771 --> 01:47:10,974
Meaning you'd better get used to it.

1035
01:47:11,024 --> 01:47:13,562
Speak for yourself, you...

1036
01:47:13,610 --> 01:47:14,641
What?

1037
01:47:18,407 --> 01:47:21,527
- What's going on?
- Nothing much. Georgette went out.

1038
01:47:21,577 --> 01:47:23,320
Joseph got mad.

1039
01:47:23,370 --> 01:47:24,865
"Went out?"

1040
01:47:24,914 --> 01:47:30,121
Just like Gina. You know who's she's with?
The guy with the plastic bag.

1041
01:47:31,837 --> 01:47:34,209
I saw their little game.

1042
01:47:34,256 --> 01:47:36,581
The note in the coat pocket,

1043
01:47:36,633 --> 01:47:38,258
4:08.

1044
01:47:38,301 --> 01:47:42,252
Back he comes, and hey presto!
Out they go.

1045
01:47:46,185 --> 01:47:49,850
- I'm worried for Amélie because I like you.
- What do you mean?

1046
01:47:50,898 --> 01:47:54,682
By and large, the men I like
are mentally unsound.

1047
01:47:54,735 --> 01:47:57,771
- I'd like to know more about you.
- Ask me questions.

1048
01:48:00,574 --> 01:48:02,366
One swallow doesn't make...?

1049
01:48:03,452 --> 01:48:04,484
A swallow?

1050
01:48:06,080 --> 01:48:07,622
A summer.

1051
01:48:07,665 --> 01:48:09,040
And clothes...?

1052
01:48:09,083 --> 01:48:10,625
The man.

1053
01:48:10,668 --> 01:48:12,078
- A good cat deserves...?
- A rat.

1054
01:48:12,127 --> 01:48:13,787
- Patience...?
- Is a virtue.

1055
01:48:13,837 --> 01:48:15,415
- Rolling stone...?
- Gathers no moss.

1056
01:48:15,464 --> 01:48:17,789
- It's a sin...?
- To steal a pin.

1057
01:48:17,841 --> 01:48:19,834
Absence makes...?

1058
01:48:19,885 --> 01:48:21,344
The heart grow fonder.

1059
01:48:21,386 --> 01:48:23,379
- Not bad.
- You collect them?

1060
01:48:23,430 --> 01:48:27,760
In my family, we say a man
who knows his proverbs can't be all bad.

1061
01:48:32,356 --> 01:48:35,807
Pretty girl from the 5th floor, listen to this!

1062
01:48:35,859 --> 01:48:38,813
- Do you believe in miracles?
- Not today.

1063
01:48:40,239 --> 01:48:42,397
You're in for a surprise.

1064
01:48:42,449 --> 01:48:45,782
What if I told you that a team of climbers

1065
01:48:45,827 --> 01:48:49,778
on Mont Blanc had found

1066
01:48:49,832 --> 01:48:54,458
hard proof that my husband loved me?

1067
01:49:27,828 --> 01:49:29,951
Lucien, I need some yeast.

1068
01:49:29,997 --> 01:49:33,912
For Miss Amélie?
She's baking her famous plum cake?

1069
01:49:33,960 --> 01:49:36,914
Collignon! Go and get the yeast.

1070
01:50:31,100 --> 01:50:32,724
Amélie?

1071
01:50:32,768 --> 01:50:33,799
Amélie?

1072
01:50:41,152 --> 01:50:42,183
Amélie?

1073
01:51:04,050 --> 01:51:05,081
[I'll be back]

1074
01:51:36,165 --> 01:51:39,166
Go into the bedroom, Miss Poulain.

1075
01:51:55,226 --> 01:51:58,345
So, little Amélie,

1076
01:51:58,396 --> 01:52:02,475
your bones aren't made of glass.

1077
01:52:02,524 --> 01:52:05,644
You can take life's knocks.

1078
01:52:05,694 --> 01:52:10,072
If you let this chance go by,

1079
01:52:10,116 --> 01:52:16,783
eventually your heart will become

1080
01:52:16,831 --> 01:52:22,869
as dry and brittle as my skeleton.

1081
01:52:24,505 --> 01:52:26,047
So...

1082
01:52:26,090 --> 01:52:29,256
Go and get him, for pete's sake!

1083
01:55:16,761 --> 01:55:22,597
[Without you, today's emotions
would be the scurf of yesterday's]

1084
01:56:18,907 --> 01:56:20,615
International airport.

1085
01:56:20,658 --> 01:56:25,700
September 28th 1997. It is exactly 11am.

1086
01:56:25,747 --> 01:56:28,451
At the funfair, near the ghost train,

1087
01:56:28,499 --> 01:56:31,666
the marshmallow twister is twisting.

1088
01:56:31,711 --> 01:56:33,999
Meanwhile, on a bench in Villette Square,

1089
01:56:34,046 --> 01:56:39,503
Félix Lerbier learns there are more links
in his brain than atoms in the universe.

1090
01:56:40,595 --> 01:56:41,710
